sections.title: MBBS Admission in Rajasthan 2025-26, Colleges Seats, Fees Structure, cut-off and Counselling

content.content: Rajasthan is a bustling center of industry, innovation, and education, celebrated for its vibrant culture, storied past, and significant economic contributions to India. Its capital.

Renowned as a premier destination for medical education in India, Rajasthan offers a plethora of undergraduate and postgraduate medical programs, drawing students from all corners of the nation. Admission to MBBS programs in Rajasthan is conducted through the NEET exam, with successful candidates participating in state counseling for enrollment.

The MBBS curriculum in Rajasthan spans 5.5 years, comprising 4.5 years of academic study and 1 year of compulsory internship, providing students with comprehensive training and practical experience.In Rajasthan aspiring MBBS students have a variety of options available for admission. The state boasts both government and private medical colleges and universities. Typically, securing admission into government medical colleges is more competitive than private ones, resulting in higher cut-off marks for government institutions.

The total number of MBBS seats in Rajasthan can vary each year due to factors such as government policies, changes in infrastructure, and accreditation of new medical colleges. For MBBS Admission Rajasthan 2025 total 4859 seats are available in Government and Private Medical Colleges in Rajasthan. The state has 1 AIIMS College located in Jodhpur and 26 Government and 9 Private Medical Colleges.

In the following sections, we will delve into the specifics of MBBS admission for the academic year 2025-26 in Rajasthan including details on college seat matrix, fee structure, application process, cut-off marks, and counseling procedures. For personalized assistance with MBBS admission in India or abroad, feel free to reach out to our dedicated admission counseling team at MBBS APP.

content.content: The NEET cutoff is determined based on various factors such as the number of applicants, the difficulty level of the exam, and the availability of seats in medical and dental colleges. It varies for different categories like General, OBC, SC, ST, and others. Each state and college may also have its own cutoff scores. Generally, higher cutoffs are seen in prestigious colleges and for popular courses. It’s crucial for aspiring medical students to keep track of cutoff trends and prepare accordingly

content.list:
• The application form must be filled out entirely online. Only online application fees are accepted from students.
  • The MBBS Admission Rajasthan Application Form is now available, and candidates can submit their applications till the deadline.
  • In order to register for the Rajasthan MBBS 2025 application form, applicants must input their personal, academic, NEET 2025 score, and other information. The authority will announce the merit ranking and adhere to the procedure of document verification, choice-filling, and place-allocation.
  • Candidates must bring a hard copy of their admissions application along with all Original Documents when they report to the designated medical or dental college; otherwise, their application will be rejected/disqualified without further communication.

sections.title: Document Required for MBBS Admission Rajasthan

content.list:
• Score Sheet for NEET 2025
  • NEET Admission Ticket
  • Letter of Assignment
  • 12th class card and passing certificate
  • Grade Card and Passing Certificate for Grade 10
  • All grade reports for classes 11 and 12, if they were passed in more than one attempt.
  • A copy of a photo identification card, such as a driver’s licence, PAN card, electoral card, government or public utility card, school ID card, or Aadhar card.
  • Valid caste certificate, sub-category certificate, if applicable
  • Certificate of domicile, if applicable
  • 4 passport size photographs same as affixed on application form
  • Character certification from the previous study institution
  • Migration Certificate from the previous study institution
  • The MBBS admission process in Rajasthan is a competitive one, but it is also a fair one. All candidates who meet the eligibility criteria have a chance to be admitted to a medical college in the state.

sections.title: Category Reservation in MBBS Admission Rajasthan

content.list:
• In accordance with government regulations, under Rajasthan NEET Counseling 2025, 15% of the seats in government colleges would be reserved for MBBS/BDS programmes on an All India basis. There will be 24 seats designated for applicants chosen from the Central Government pool, 4 in each of Rajasthan’s State Medical Colleges (6 Government colleges). These positions will be filled by the Central Government Authority.
  • The remaining 85% of seats are covered by the state quota and will be filled in the Rajasthan MBBS and BDS admissions 2025 on the basis of merit and preference, with reservations for the following categories

content.content: Q: How many Medical Colleges are there in Rajasthan offering MBBS 2026?
Ans: There are 26 Government medical colleges including of ESIC Alwar, one AIIMS -Jodhpur and 09 private medical colleges in Rajasthan.
Q: Is there any fee relaxation for SC/ST/Female candidates in Govt. and Semi Govt. Medical Colleges of Rajasthan?
Ans: Yes, fee relaxation is there in some Govt. Medical Colleges of Rajasthan.
Q: Is there any NRI Quota in Government Medical Colleges of Rajasthan?
How many seats are there under NRI Quota in Rajasthan?
Ans: Yes, NRI Quota is there in Government medical colleges of Rajasthan. There are 381 MBBS seats in Rajasthan under NRI quota.
Q: What is Rajasthan MBBS Admission Counselling Website?
Ans: www.rajneetug2023.com for NEET Counselling 2025.
Q: How many Government MBBS Colleges are in Rajasthan 2023?
Ans: There are 26 Government medical colleges and as far as MBBS seats are concerned total seats are (3446+1032 Management Quota +381 NRI quota) MBBS Seats in Rajasthan for session 2025-26.
Q: What is NRI Quota MBBS fee in Rajasthan Government Medical Colleges?
Ans: As far as MBBS fee under NRI quota is concerned it $ 34728.75 per annum in Government medical colleges of Rajasthan.
Q: When will Rajasthan Second Round NEET UG Counselling will start?
Ans: After completion of all India Quota Counselling Round 2, State Round 2 Counselling to start. for every State separate Notification for Round 2 Counselling will be there.
Q: Whether Rajasthan Second Round of Counselling will be online or offline?
Ans: Although Registration will be online and after successful registration merit list will be released but final admission will be offline at RUHS, Dental College Jaipur.
Q: Is it possible to get admission in state Govt. Medical Colleges under NRI Quota?
Ans: Yes, if you are willing to take admission in Govt. College with low NEET Score you can apply under NRI Quota and can take seat.
Q: Rajasthan MBBS BDS Second Round & Mop Up Round Counselling will be online or offline in 2025?
Ans: Rajasthan MBBS BDS Second Round & Mop Up Round Counselling will be conducted offline in 2025 at RUHS Dental college.
